user.biography:
🤓 Enjoying my geeky life
🎮 I do cosplay and stream videogames
🗻 My adventures: @irina.away 
Business: irina@mediaw.net
SMTH INTERESTING 😜⬇️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Irina Meier in Las Vegas Nevada with @kojaikosti, and @alicenevermindart. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text:
MORE THAN 10 YEARS OF DOING COSPLAY. WHAT'S NEXT?

Today cosplay is a massive part of geek culture and there are hundreds of people in this field who managed to turn their hobby into a full time job and it's amazing!

On the other side, it gives a feeling of... competition? A few years ago in average a cosplayer could create maybe from 3 to 6 costumes per year, but now some people are able to do THAT MANY each month! 

It makes you feel like a loser if you don't match that pace. It makes you feel that you are not as good as the others...

I always wanted to try different things on Instagram, but I did not, because I thought that "people are here just for the cosplay content" and if I do something different THEY WILL ALL LEAVE...

What an idiot I've been 🤣

And do you know what happened? 
A MASSIVE BURNOUT IN 2018. 
To the point that I wanted to quit cosplay. 

What saved me? Simply asking myself "WTF am I doing and for who?" 
Long time ago I started cosplaying as a little 11 y.o. girl and this process was... sacred?
It felt like Christmas every time I did my first ugly makeup attempts, trying to draw anime eyes on my pimply teenage face with very mediocre makeup skills and cheap cosmetics from AliExpress 🤣
But how happy I was! You have no idea! 

All I want is to keep this excitement! To make projects which really mean a lof to me and have fun in the process! Even if I produce not so many cosplays per year. 

In the meantime, please enjoy my non cosplay projects too 😉 This month you can discover me as Showgirl. What an amazing hobby I have! Last month I was a military lady - today a shiny dancer in a plastic costume 🤣 

Thank you for sharing that passion with me ❤️ 

P.S. You know where to find the full photoshoot 😉 (linк in biо)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Irina Meier on June 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
Let’s talk about pretending 🙂

See this photo? It’s me surrounded by greenery, enjoying a pleasant summer day... Right?

In fact it’s 45°C / 113°F, me dying of heat and a cramp in my leg after staying too much in the same pose 😂 

Sometimes beautiful photos are made through pain lol 

And it’s just casual photos. The dark side of cosplay sometimes is even more painful. I think I should share with you some fun stories from my photoshoots in extreme conditions hahahahaha

Btw, this is my second photoshoot of the month on my Ратreоn and today is the last day to get it together with my Peggy Carter 😊😋just saying ❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Irina Meier on June 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text:
It's time to admit.. I think I'm really into women in uniform 🥺👉🏻👈🏻🧡

Okay, first I cosplayed Olivier Mira Armstrong from #FMA and I loved it, but after Peggy Carter I can say it for sure - a strict looking uniform is my thing! 😂

It's funny, when I was in school I had a lot of problems, because I didn't follow the dress code... (we had strict uniforms in school). Good old times when rebellious Irina tried to enter school in jeans (it was the biggest crime at that time😂)

And now I'm 24 and look at me? I'm eager to wear these uncomfortable jackets and skirts (but just for a photoshoot 😂)

Do you like uniforms on me?
If yes, you know where to find the full photoshoot 😉
Or if you don't know, it's called Раtrе0n and it's the last 48 hours to get this photoshoot together with another pretty project of this month (I will post a teaser tomorrow) 😜❤️ linк in biо

#agentcarter #peggycarter #captainamerica #marvel #cosplay #marvelcosplay #uniform

node.text:
DO YOU LIKE GIFTS? I HAVE SOMETHING FOR YOU ⬇️😜🎉

Okay, I'm a massive fan of Castlevania on Netflix, but I've never played the original games... Because I was not born at the time lmao 🤣🙈

But thanks to @limitedrungames
I can play the limited edition of the legendary original games and...

WE WANT TO GIVE 3 GAMES TO YOU! 😜❤️

1 of you will get the ultimate collector edition pack and 2 others will get the physical game.

All you need to do is to like this post and write in the comments who is your favorite monster of all time. I'll pick the winners in 48 hours! 

P.S. For those interested in rare physical collectible games, check out @limitedrungames ! They really do amazing and nostalgic things 😍

P.P.S. Lenore cosplay is coming very very soon 😉

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Irina Meier on June 19, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
Swimsuit for Instagram VS Swimsuit for real life 🤣➡️

Yeah, after getting crazy sunburns in January I prefer to be fully covered during the day #vampireproblems 🧛🏻‍♀️

So many people I know are dreaming about chill vacations near the sea, but...

Strangely I'm more in the mood for snowy mountains 😂 I checked some videos from my trip to Cuzco and nostalgia hit me hard hehe
Unfortunately pretty much all countries I want to visit are closed for me now 😭💔

Can't wait for us to beat this virus, for borders to reopen and for amazing adventures to begin. And now I'll have virtual adventures on my Switch with Subnautica in the swimming pool hehe

Where would you like to go when the worldwide situation gets better? 🤔😊

#summer

node.text:
Talking about legs... 😂👠

Just wanted to share with you a new photo from one of the most impromptu photoshoots in my life!😱

I always loved Peggy Carter, but never really planned to make a cosplay of her. I saw that beautiful @stormborncat was selling this cosplay and I was just like: OMG I DON'T KNOW WHY, BUT I NEED IT 😂😂🤣🤣

So here we go, I'm happy to present you my take on an amazing strong lady of the Marvel universe. What do you think? Does this character suits me? 😊

This full photoshoot will be the main reward (together with another special photoshoot😏) for my Ратrons on Ратreon in June :) 

P.S. I'm thankful from the bottom of my heart for all the sweet messages you sent me these last few days! You make me smile and I really appreciate it ❤️🙏🏻

#cosplay #marvel #peggycarter #captainamerica #avengers #oldschool #army

node.text:
"YOUR LEGS ARE FAT, YOU SHOULD LOSE WEIGHT"... 🐖🐷

... some people said under my previous post.

What surprised me the most is how many DMs I received yesterday from women and men who shared their stories about being bullied because of their appearance. Or how they were struggling to accept themselves because of the crazy beauty standards (which frequently are absolutely ridiculous and disconnected from reality)!

You know, I was always kind of a hard-shell person, so I was less sensitive to hurful comments, BUT…! 

What hurts me the most is the fact that there are so many people who are much more sensitive and will be affected by that! They struggle with eating disorders and acceptance of themselves for years, because some idiots once told them that they are ugly! 🙈

I always had big legs, which are not really fitting common beauty standards of women, BUT I LOVE THEM! As much as I like to eat delicious fatty food sometimes 😂 

So I don't even want to make this post about those who can't control their language. I just want to say to all of you, that YOU ARE BEAUTIFUL NO MATTER WHAT!❤️

And if someone's ever told you the opposite, F*CK ‘EM, THEY ARE MORONS! 😂

node.text:
Sorry for the silly video, I'm just having fun after a photoshoot 🤣🎶

Do you have a song which always cheers you up? Or a song that makes you dance each time?

I'm ashamed to say, but for me it's "Billionaire" 🤣 Yeah, I know.. But it's so positive and catchy. It literally makes me smile every time I hear it hahaha

I also love BTS and many other Korean bands! Can't stand still when I hear BTS - Butter! 😍🤣

Anyway, please share with me your fav songs in the comments ❤️

#dance #music

node.text:
MY SUFFERING FACE WHEN IT'S TIME TO DO LAUNDRY 😣

Just kidding! Actually it's one of my favorite home chores. I guess I just love the smell of washing powder and fresh clean clothes 😂❤️

But you know what is the absolute worst thing for me?

... Cooking! 🍳

For some reasons it always stresses me out and I feel very exhausted after cleaning all the mess generated by my "Michelin cooking" attempts 😂 So most of the time my fridge looks like the cliche fridge of a single student guy filled with tons of plastic packs with pre-made food hahahahaha

Good for me that my whole life I’ve been surrounded by people who adore cooking 😂🤣🙈

What is your most hated home chore? And what do you do with pleasure?

P.S. Btw, this pinup photoshoot will be available on my Patreon for the Patrons of this month and it includes A LOT of pretty photos you may enjoy very much 😉❤️
